 Candidate C is not very willing to further his education.\n- Candidate C puts concern for others above everything.\n- Candidate C has excellent attention skills.\n\n- Candidate D responds to unexpected events adequately.\n- Candidate D can concentrate very well.\n- Candidate D solves problems extremely well.\n- Candidate D takes responsibility seriously.\n- Candidate D is considered moody.\n- Candidate D is regarded as a loner.\n\nNote: Some attributes from earlier discussion (like \"uncooperative\", \"grumpy\", \"hot temper\") are not in the list; those were from other agents? Actually Agent 1's data included \"uncooperative\" and \"grumpy\"? The initial list didn't include those. The list we have is the only official data. So we must not use attributes not in our list. So we must correct: Candidate B is \"pretentious\" and \"wrong tone\". Not \"uncooperative\" or \"grumpy\". Candidate D is \"moody\" and \"loner\". Not \"hot temper\". So we must adjust.\n\nThus we need to evaluate based on these attributes.\n\nWe need to consider all criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness, decision-making, teamwork, professional development.\n\nLet's assess each candidate:\n\nA: Anticipates dangerous situations (reliability/judgment). Sees complex connections (cognitive). Excellent spatial vision (technical). Very good leadership (teamwork). Unfriendly (teamwork negative). Eats unhealthily (maybe health, but not directly relevant). No explicit stress/calmness info. No explicit decision speed. No explicit professional development.\n\nB: Very conscientious (reliability). Handles stress very well (calmness). Good at assessing weather (technical). Excellent computer skills (technical). Pretentious (teamwork negative). Sometimes adopts wrong tone (communication negative). No explicit decision speed. No explicit leadership.\n\nC: Can make correct decisions quickly (decision-making). Difficulty communicating ideas (teamwork negative). Egocentric (teamwork negative). Not willing to further education (professional development negative). Puts concern for others above everything (teamwork positive). Excellent attention skills (cognitive). No explicit stress/calmness, but no mention. No explicit technical except attention.\n\nD: Responds to unexpected events adequately (judgment). Can concentrate very well (cognitive). Solves problems extremely well (technical/cognitive). Takes responsibility seriously (reliability). Moody (teamwork negative). Loner (teamwork negative). No explicit stress/calmness.\n\nThus weigh: B has stress handling and conscientiousness, but pretentious and wrong tone may affect crew. A has strong anticipation, leadership, but unfriendly may affect crew. C has quick decision, concern for others, but communication issues and egocentric, not willing to develop. D has problem solving and responsibility, but moody and loner.\n\nWe need to decide provisional preference. We should consider which weaknesses are more severe. For long-distance flights, calmness under pressure is crucial. B explicitly handles stress well. A unknown. D unknown. C unknown. So B's stress handling is a strong point. However, teamwork is also crucial; pretentious and wrong tone could be problematic but maybe manageable. A's unfriendly also problematic. B's pretentious may be similar. Which candidate has best overall? B has strong stress handling, conscientiousness, technical skills (weather, computer). Teamwork issues but maybe less severe than A's unfriendly? Both are negative. C's communication difficulty is severe. D's moody and loner also severe.\n\nThus B might be best despite teamwork issues. We should ask other agents if they have any positive teamwork info for B or negative for A? But we have already asked about stress for A and D. We could ask Agent 1 about Candidate A's teamwork or communication style? Agent 1's data includes \"unfriendly\". Already known. Could ask Agent 2 about Candidate B's teamwork? Agent 2's data includes pretentious and wrong tone. Already known. Could ask Agent 1 about Candidate D's stress? Already no info. So we have all.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate B.\n\nWe need to state uncertainty: lack of info on A's stress handling, D's calmness, C's calmness. Also B's teamwork issues could be mitigated.\n\nWe need to reference evidence from others: Agent 2's provisional preference for A, but we disagree. We need to mention that we have data on B's stress handling (from our list) and that others have not provided that. Also mention that Agent 1 and Agent 2 have no data on B's teamwork beyond pretentious and wrong tone.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing.\n\nMETADATA_JSON with vote \"Candidate B\"."}
