ting ideas (teamwork negative)\n- Egocentric (teamwork negative)\n- Not very willing to further his education (professional development negative)\n- Puts concern for others above everything (teamwork positive)\n- Excellent attention skills (cognitive)\n\nCandidate D:\n- Responds to unexpected events adequately (judgment)\n- Can concentrate very well (cognitive)\n- Solves problems extremely well (technical/cognitive)\n- Takes responsibility seriously (reliability)\n- Considered moody (teamwork negative)\n- Regarded as a loner (teamwork negative)\n\nNow weigh for long-distance pilot: key criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nWe have explicit calmness only for B. So B has a clear advantage there. B also conscientious, good technical (weather, computer). Weakness: pretentious, wrong tone. Those are communication/teamwork issues but not necessarily fatal; could be mitigated.\n\nA has strong anticipation, leadership, spatial vision, but no calmness data, and unfriendly. Unfriendly could affect crew. No data on stress.\n\nC has quick correct decisions, attention, concern for others (positive), but communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education. No calmness data.\n\nD has responsibility, problem solving, concentration, but moody, loner, no calmness data.\n\nThus B seems strongest overall given explicit calmness and technical competence. The negative traits are communication style, but we have no data on severity. According to grounding rule, we must weigh weaknesses as evidence, not mitigate. So pretentious and wrong tone are negative evidence. But B also has positive stress handling, which is crucial. Others lack that.\n\nThus I think provisional preference should be Candidate B.\n\nWe should also consider if any other agent might have info on calmness for A, C, D. We have asked about A and D earlier, no info. No one has info on C's calmness. So B remains only candidate with explicit calmness.\n\nThus I will state my current position: Candidate B, with confidence moderate, but note uncertainties: lack of calmness data for others, and communication issues for B.\n\nWe should also ask if any other agent has any positive teamwork info for B beyond what we have? Already we have all. Could ask Agent 1 if they have any additional info on B's teamwork? Agent 1's data includes only what we have. So no.\n\nThus final answer: public message summarizing.\n\nProceed."}
