ponds to unexpected events adequately\n- can concentrate very well\n- solves problems extremely well\n- takes responsibility seriously\n- considered moody\n- regarded as a loner\n- regarded as arrogant (Agent 2)\n- relatively weak leadership skills (Agent 2)\n- regarded as a know-it-all (Agent 1/3)\n- hot temper (Agent 1/3)\n\nNow evaluate criteria:\n\nReliability/responsibility: A (anticipates dangerous, leadership), B (very conscientious, handles stress), C (quick correct decisions, puts concern for others), D (takes responsibility seriously, solves problems, responds to unexpected events).\n\nTechnical/cognitive competence: A (spatial vision, complex connections), B (weather assessment, computer), C (understands complicated technology, excellent attention), D (problem solving, concentration).\n\nCalmness/judgment under pressure: B handles stress very well, C keeps calm in crisis, D responds adequately to unexpected events (but also hot temper/moody), A unknown.\n\nDecision-making speed: C quick correct decisions, A anticipates dangerous, D solves problems extremely well, B not explicit.\n\nTeamwork/communication: A leadership but unfriendly, show-off, not open to new ideas, unorganized, criticism issues. B pretentious, wrong tone, grumpy, uncooperative, nasty remarks, weak memory for numbers. C difficulty communicating, egocentric, but puts concern for others above everything. D moody, loner, know-it-all, arrogant, weak leadership.\n\nProfessional development: A not open to new ideas, unorganized. B conscientious, but no mention of development. C not willing to further education. D takes responsibility, but moody.\n\nNow weigh for long-distance pilot: stress handling is crucial. B explicit, C also keeps calm in crisis (good). D has hot temper, moody (negative). A unknown.\n\nTeamwork is also crucial. B has many negative interpersonal traits (pretentious, grumpy, uncooperative, nasty remarks). C also has communication difficulty and egocentric, but also puts concern for others above everything. A has unfriendly, show-off, not open to new ideas. D is loner, moody, know-it-all.\n\nWhich candidate balances? B has stress handling but severe teamwork issues. C has calmness, quick decisions, crew concern, but communication difficulty and egocentric, plus unwillingness to develop. A has strong anticipation and leadership but unknown stress, and negative interpersonal. D has responsibility and problem solving but hot temper and moody.\n\nGiven long-distance flights require crew coordination, stress handling, and decision making. B's stress handling is strong, but his interpersonal issues could jeopardize crew resource management. C's calmness and crew concern may offset communication issues? But difficulty communicating ideas is serious for cockpit communication. Egocentric also problematic.\n\nA's leadership could help crew, but unknown stress handling is a big gap.\n\nThus we need to decide. Perhaps the best is Candidate B because stress handling is explicit and essential, and technical competence is strong. The teamwork issues are serious but may be mitigated with training; other candidates have even more severe issues (C's communication difficulty, D's hot temper, A's unfriendly and lack of stress data). So I will vote Candidate B.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing key evidence, evidence from others, alternatives, tradeoff, uncertainty, what would change vote. And METADATA_JSON with agent \"agent_2\" and vote \"Candidate B\"."}
